{[%evp 0,49,32,26,17,13,12,12,12,-1,-1,-1,15,15,16,16,16,16,39,33,33,33,33,35,
35,35,35,65,65,57,68,41,47,47,64,40,40,40,40,40,53,53,40,54,54,48,48,48,48,48,
60,59]} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 Nbd7 6. O-O c6 7. a4 b6
{has been tried in some high-level games.} 8. Nfd2 {if we take on c4, our
position is just better, but we must check the critical move} Ba6 9. Bxc6 {
necessary.} Rc8 10. Bb5 $1 {Very important move to remember.} (10. Bg2 {
was played in some games, but after} Nb8 $1 {Black's position is just fine.
For example:} 11. Nf3 (11. e3 Bb4 $11 {[%cal Ge8g8] 00 next.}) 11... Bb7 $1 $11
{[%cal Yf8e7,Ye7b4,Ye8g8] Be7 (or Bb4) and 00 next.}) 10... Bb7 {only move.}
11. Nc3 h5 {This is Black's idea.} (11... Be7 12. Bxc4 O-O 13. b3 $14 {Black
doesn't have enough compensation, and White is better. One day, we might
consider e3-Be2-Bf3.}) 12. e4 $1 {[%csl Rb7] White's best, with the idea to
limit the activity of Black's Bb7.} h4 {Most common continuation.} (12... Bb4 {
Was played only in Flom-Visakh, but it's a normal move.} 13. e5 $1 $146 Ng4 14.
Nde4 {looks very bad for Black, but maybe with concrete moves he can survive:}
(14. Bxc4 $5 {might be another way:} O-O 15. Be2 f6 $1 16. Qb3 Qe7 17. Nde4 $14
{For now looks slightly better for White, and it's new position.}) 14... a6 $1
15. h3 axb5 16. hxg4 hxg4 17. Qxg4 Kf8 18. f3 $1 {[%csl Rb7] Important move.}
f5 $1 {Only move for Black.} 19. exf6 Nxf6 20. Nxf6 Qxf6 21. axb5 $14 {[%cal
Ga1a7] New position, and it seems that White is slightly better. Of course, if
one day this position will have 100 games, maybe it will be considered fine
for Black, but for now it's definitely interesting for White.}) 13. Qe2 (13. g4
{was played in Gelfand-Erigaisi, but after} Bb4 14. Qe2 O-O $13 {The position
looks very unclear. Sometimes Black can play Nh7 idea.}) 13... hxg3 (13... Bb4
$2 14. e5 hxg3 15. fxg3 O-O 16. Rf4 $1 $16 {Advantage.}) 14. fxg3 Be7 $1 {
Fantastic engine's idea. The point is that after} (14... Bb4 $2 {trans in 13...
Bb4.}) 15. e5 {Black plays} O-O $3 {Incredible idea.} 16. Rf4 {my
recommendation.} (16. exf6 Nxf6 $44 {It seems that Black has full compensation.
}) 16... Nd5 17. Nxd5 $1 Bxd5 18. Nxc4 {It's a new position. Looks better for
White, but Black can play the strong} f5 $1 19. Ne3 Nb8 $1 20. Nxd5 Qxd5 21.
Be3 a6 22. Bd3 Bg5 23. Rf2 Bxe3 24. Qxe3 Rcd8 $1 {Move by move the position is
getting closer to equality, but it's still fresh, and it's difficult that your
opponent will play all the best moves.} 25. Rc1 Qxd4 26. Qxd4 Rxd4 27. Bc4 Re8
28. Rf4 Rd2 $1 29. Rxf5 Rxb2 30. Rf2 Rxf2 31. Kxf2 $14 {/= In the worst case,
we can play this endgame. If your opponents knows also here, then it will be a
draw, but I think it's very unlikely it will happen soon.} *

