{[%evp 0,25,20,20,15,15,15,15,14,-10,7,-11,41,54,36,31,46,27,34,16,4,4,-10,0,0,
-26,-40,-13]} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 b5 $6 {Nowdays,
it's not easy to call a line "absolutely bad", because the super engines are
able to find defensive resources everywhere. But the 5...b5 line is really bad
actually :)} 6. a4 c6 7. Ne5 Nd5 {Most common move.} ({Black has also tried} 
7... Bb4+ 8. Nc3 Nd5 {but White is much better after} 9. axb5 $1 cxb5 (9...
Nxc3 10. bxc3 Bxc3+ 11. Bd2 Qxd4 (11... Bxa1 12. Qxa1 $18 {Winning for White.})
12. Nf3 Bxd2+ 13. Nxd2 $16 {Big advantage.}) 10. O-O Bxc3 11. bxc3 Nxc3 12. Qc2
Nd5 13. Ba3 $16 {[%csl Re8][%cal Ge2e4] e4 next, Black's king is still in the
center, White has a big advantage.}) 8. O-O a6 (8... Bb7 {Black's main line,
but after} 9. axb5 $1 cxb5 10. b3 {It's very possible that Black's position is
just lost.} cxb3 (10... Nd7 11. bxc4 Nxe5 12. cxd5 Nc4 13. dxe6 Bxg2 14. exf7+
Kxf7 15. Kxg2 $16 {Full extra pawn, but the advantage is bigger than +1,00.})
11. Qxb3 a6 12. e4 $1 Nf6 13. d5 $18 {Winning position for White.}) 9. axb5
cxb5 10. Nc3 Bb7 11. Nxd5 $1 exd5 {Also bad because of} (11... Bxd5 {Bad
because of} 12. e4 Bb7 13. d5 $18) 12. e4 $1 dxe4 13. Qh5 $1 g6 14. Nxg6 $1
fxg6 15. Qe5+ Qe7 16. Qxh8 Nd7 {now we need to remember} 17. h4 $1 O-O-O 18.
Bg5 Qf7 {Millet-Navrotescu, 2022. White played Bh3, but much stronger was} 19.
Bxd8 $1 $146 Bg7 20. Qxh7 Nf8 21. Qxg7 Qxg7 22. Bg5 $18 {Equal material, but
we have very powerful bishops, ad probably Black's position is lost. In
conclusion, 5...b5 is a very dubious continuation. I cannot guarantee that
Black's position is objectively lost, but if you study this file well, you
will definitely have the advantage.} *

