{[%evp 0,45,21,24,29,11,13,14,14,-8,-13,4,-5,-17,3,-5,-11,-11,-11,1,4,-9,0,-17,
-17,0,-28,-20,-15,15,23,-3,55,55,28,56,47,47,47,47,47,40,61,46,64,51,53,50]} 1.
d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 Bd7 6. Ne5 Nc6 7. Nxc4 {[%csl Yc6,
Yd7][%cal Rc7c5] Black doesn't have a healthy position, there is no c5, the
bishop is on d7 is not great, the knight on c6 also, but there are some games.}
b5 $5 {is probably the most interesting way to play for Black.} (7... Bb4+ 8.
Nc3 Nd5 {There was a game Giri-Kuzubov, where Giri played 9.Bd2, but} 9. O-O
$146 {I suggest to play this move.} (9. Bd2 Nb6 {Black's position is more or
less acceptable.}) (9. Qd3 $5 {another serious move, played in Van
Wely-Harikrishna.}) 9... Nxc3 10. bxc3 Bxc3 11. Rb1 {We create counterplay on
the b7 pawn.} Rb8 12. Rb3 {Strong move.} Bb4 {Only move.} (12... Bxd4 $4 13.
Rd3 $18 {Black can resign.}) 13. e4 {We get the center in exchange for the
pawn.} b5 14. Ne3 {A very good square for the knight.} Bd6 (14... Be7 15. d5 {
is strong now because after} exd5 16. Nxd5 {The bishop is not well placed on
e7.} O-O 17. Bf4 {[%csl Re7] We have this extra option.} Bd6 18. Rd3 $1 {
Important move, and Black is worse. Best line is:} Bxf4 19. Nxf4 Ne5 20. Rd5
Qe7 21. Rxe5 Qxe5 22. Qxd7 $16 {Material is equal, but our pieces are very
strong.}) (14... O-O $2 15. d5 $18) 15. e5 {is stronger.} (15. d5 exd5 16. exd5
(16. Nxd5 O-O $13 {Black is absolutely fine.}) 16... Na5 $13) 15... Be7 16. d5
$1 {White has a very promising initiative after for example:} Nxe5 17. Bb2 f6 {
Best move.} 18. Bxe5 $5 fxe5 19. Ng4 $36 {Very interesting position.}) 8. Ne5
$1 {We go back to e5, very important move.} (8. Nca3 {was played in the game
Sadwhani-Short, but after} Rb8 $11 {Black was fine.}) 8... Nxe5 9. dxe5 Nd5 10.
O-O {There was only one game here.} c5 {This is the best.} (10... Be7 {1-0
Halkias,S (2530)-Nabaty,T (2658) EU-chT 22nd Batumi 2019 (6.3)} 11. Nc3 $146 {
is my recommendation.} Nxc3 12. bxc3 Rb8 13. Qd4 c5 14. Qg4 $16 {Castle is met
with Bh6, looks bad for Black, not easy to find a good move.}) 11. Bxd5 exd5
12. Qxd5 {Black plays for compensation on the light squares, but I don't think
it is enough.} Rc8 13. Nc3 $5 {Immediate Rd1 is also interesting.} b4 14. Ne4
Bh3 15. Rd1 Qxd5 16. Rxd5 $14 {[%cal Ge4d6] It is a promising endgame for
White, maybe Black can hold with engine, but very difficult to play.} *

