{[%evp 0,45,21,24,29,11,13,14,14,-8,-13,4,-5,-17,3,-5,-11,-11,-11,1,4,-9,0,-17,
-17,0,-28,-20,-15,15,23,-3,55,55,28,56,47,47,47,47,47,40,61,46,64,51,53,50]} 1.
d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 Bd7 6. Ne5 Bc6 7. Nxc6 Nxc6 8. O-O
Qd7 9. e3 O-O-O {[%csl Rc8][%cal Gh7h5,Gh5h4] Historically, this was Black's
plan, to castle long and play h5-h4, but this line is almost refuted, because
it was proven that Black's king on c8 is potentially in big danger.} 10. Nc3 $5
{[%cal Ye6e5] e5 was a threat, for this reason, Nc3 is a good move.} (10. b3 $6
{is our general idea, but it is premature because of} e5 $15 {Black is maybe
even slightly better.}) (10. Qa4 {is the main move, but after} Nd5 11. Qxc4 h5
$132 {The advantage is smaller and maybe Black can have a game.}) 10... Nd5 {
was played in Sasikiran-Ponomariov, but also in other games.} (10... h5 {
Concrete move, we can continue our plan.} 11. b3 Bb4 {is Black's idea.} (11...
cxb3 $2 {Of course, it is very dangerous.} 12. Qxb3 Nd5 13. Rb1 b6 14. Bd2 $18
{[%cal Gf1c1] All our pieces join the game, objectively lost position.}) 12.
Bb2 Bxc3 {is probably more sound than the other moves.} (12... cxb3 $2 {
was played in Jianu-Gholami, but it is a very bad choice.} 13. Qxb3 Nd5 14.
Nxd5 exd5 15. Rfc1 {Very big advantage.} Ba5 {Black tried to place the bishop
on b6.} 16. Rc5 $16 {[%cal Gc5d5] White missed this move, winning the d5 pawn,
terrible for Black.}) (12... e5 {has been tried in some games, but here we are
better after} 13. bxc4 exd4 {is a better try.} (13... Bxc3 $2 {Very bad.} 14.
Bxc3 exd4 15. exd4 Nxd4 16. Rb1 {We are following some games.} c6 17. Bxd4 Qxd4
18. Qb3 Qb6 19. Qa3 $1 {Very strong move.} Qa6 20. Bh3+ {is a more
straightforward win.} (20. Qxa6 bxa6 21. Bxc6 $16 {Advantage, probably also
winning position. 1-0 (59) Heimisson,H (2323)-Mitusov,S (2415) Gothenburg
Manhem 2022 (5)}) 20... Kc7 21. Qe7+ Kb8 22. Qxf7 $18 {[%csl Rb8,Gg7] Equal
material, but +5 according to the engine.}) 14. exd4 h4 {is the best according
to the engine, but White still has a big advantage after} (14... Nxd4 $2 {
was played by the chinese player, Lu Miaoyi, she actually improved a lot over
the last 3 years, but the move just loses.} 15. Nd5 {White wins back all the
material.} Nxd5 16. cxd5 Nb5 17. Bxg7 Rhg8 18. Qxh5 $18 {1-0 Panesar,V (2291)
-Lu,M (2241) Novi Sad TS Mix 224th 2021 (8)}) 15. d5 $16 {There is no clear
win, but it's still +1 something.}) 13. Bxc3 Nd5 {This is the point, if White
moves the bishop, c4-c3 is possible.} 14. Rc1 $1 {That's why this move is
important.} (14. Be1 c3 $13 {Black closes some lines on the queenside.}) 14...
cxb3 15. Qxb3 {We follow the game Gelfand-Harika.} h4 16. Rb1 {A good move.} (
16. Rc2 $5 {was maybe even more precise.} hxg3 17. hxg3 f5 {[%csl Rc2]
Compared to the game, the White rook is already on c2, so it's like an extra
tempo.} 18. Rb1 b6 19. Rbc1 $16 {We can already double the rooks, with big
problems for Black.}) 16... b6 17. Rfc1 hxg3 18. hxg3 f5 {[%cal Gg7g5,Gd7h7,
Gh7h2,Gg1f1] It takes a lot of time, just to put create a threat a check on h2,
and even then we can just move Kf1 and no mate.} 19. a4 $5 {Maybe was better,
with a5 ideas.} (19. Be1 {1-0 (47) Gelfand,B (2734)-Harika,D (2514) Eurasia
Blitz Chess Cup Almaty 2016 (1)}) 19... a5 20. Qc4 $16 {looks very difficult
for Black.}) (10... e5 $2 {is not good now, because White can play} 11. Qa4 {
Even stronger.} (11. d5 {As minimum.}) 11... exd4 12. exd4 $16 {The bishop is
too strong, seems terrible for Black.}) (10... Kb8 {If Black just waits} 11. b3
$18 {is our idea, Black is already losing.}) 11. Bd2 {[%csl Yc3,Rc8][%cal
Gb2b3] We support the knight on c3 and prepare b3.} h5 (11... Bb4 12. Na4 $5 {
is stronger, in my opinion.} (12. Qe2 {was played in the aforementioned game,
but after} Nb6 {It was a game. 1-0 (73) Sasikiran,K (2639)-Ponomariov,R (2710)
Wch Rapid Berlin 2015 (11)}) 12... Bxd2 13. Qxd2 e5 {is the best.} (13... Nb6
14. Nc5 $16 {[%cal Gb2b4] Now we have the fantastic square for the knight.})
14. Rfc1 exd4 15. exd4 {White has a very big attack.} b6 16. Qe2 Na5 {Attacks
the knight and defends c4, but} 17. b3 {Black has serious problems with the
king.} Rhe8 (17... cxb3 $4 {It's game over.} 18. Nc5 $18 {[%cal Ge2a6]}) 18.
Qf3 $16 {It looks very bad for Black, +1.50.}) 12. b3 {Our plan.} cxb3 (12...
Nb6 13. bxc4 Nxc4 14. Rb1 $16 {Same story as in all the lines, big attack and
problems with the king.}) 13. Qxb3 {We don't need to rush with Nxd5.} Na5 14.
Qc2 Nc4 {When Black tries to play such moves, it's already a bad sign.} 15. Ne4
{The knights are not stable.} Na3 {was played in a game between a 2000 vs 2500.
} 16. Qb3 {is obviously much better.} (16. Qc1 $2 {This was a bad move, Black
won.}) 16... Qb5 {Probably White was scared of exchanging the queens, but
there is a strong idea.} 17. Ng5 $1 {And Black is probably lost after} Rd7 18.
e4 Nb6 19. d5 $18 {If exd5, Bh3 ideas.} *

