{[%evp 0,25,27,27,27,20,18,18,9,-5,-4,-5,-4,5,5,-6,-1,-53,0,5,0,0,0,0,45,45,26,
17]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 c5 {This is Black's
classical line in the 4...dxc4 Catalan.} 6. O-O Nc6 7. Ne5 $5 {This is my
recommendation. It's only the third most popular move for White, and maybe
your opponent will not be so well-prepared against it. Also, I think that the
arising positions are very rich and interesting to play.} (7. dxc5 {This is
the endgame option. After} Qxd1 8. Rxd1 Bxc5 9. Nbd2 c3 10. bxc3 O-O 11. Nb3
Be7 {You can try to play this endgame, but you play for a very small advantage,
and more than 1000 games have been played here. Of course, 7.dxc5 is not a bad
choice, but I want to offer you something where you will most likely surprise
your opponent.}) 7... Bd7 {Black's best move.} (7... Nxe5 {Has been played in
more than 600 games, and we will check it in "Position 1" of this Unit.}) 8.
Nxc4 $5 {Once again, we choose a less common direction. 8.Na3 and 8.Nxc6 are
more popular, but 8.Nxc4 is more fresh and interesting, in my opinion.} cxd4 9.
Bf4 {Now, Black has two possible continuations:} Nd5 {Is Black's most common
continuation. After} (9... Be7 10. Nd6+ Kf8 {[%csl Rf8] Black's king on f8
looks bad, but the game is concrete.} 11. Nxb7 Qb6 12. Nd6 {We will check this
in "Position 2" of this Unit, but let me mention that after} Qc5 $1 {best move.
} 13. Ne4 $5 {Will be my recommendation, and it has been played only in nine
games. This means that we need to start the analysis in a very fresh position,
where there is still a lot to invent.}) 10. Nd6+ Bxd6 11. Bxd6 Nde7 {[%cal
Ge8g8] Black is ready to castle, and we will check this in "Position 3" of
this Unit.} 12. Nd2 O-O 13. Qb3 {Now, Black can choose between Bc8 and b6, but
only 39 games in this position, so once again, we need to analyze something
very fresh. I am sure that my recommendation against the 5...c5 will be a
surprise for your opponent, and that you will be able to enjoy many memorable
and interesting games!} *

