6. O-O Nc6 7. Ne5 Nxe5 {This is Black's second most important move, and it has
been played in almost 700 games.} (7... Nxd4 $4 {Is a terrible mistake because
of} 8. e3 $18) (7... Nd5 {Possible move, but not dangerous for us.} 8. Na3 Nxd4
(8... cxd4 9. Nxc6 bxc6 10. Qxd4 {[%csl Ra7,Rc4,Rc6] We are better because of
Black's bad pawn structure. In case of} Qb6 {We can play} 11. Qg4 $5 $14) 9.
Naxc4 Be7 {Black has an extra pawn, but after we play} 10. e3 Nc6 {only move}
11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. Qa4 {[%csl Ra7,Rc5,Rc6] We can play against Black's
structure.} O-O 13. Rd1 {[%cal Ge3e4] our idea is e4} (13. Qxc6 $2 {Don't take
the pawn immediately, better to play for activity.}) 13... Qc7 14. Bd2 $14 {
[%cal Gd2a5] Sometimes we have Ba5. It's a new position, and it's clear that
White is better.}) 8. dxe5 Qxd1 {Black tries his luck in the endgame.} (8...
Nd5 $6 9. Na3 {[%csl Yd6][%cal Ga3c4,Ye2e4,Yc4d6] Our plan is very simple:
Nxc4, then e4, and our knight might jump later on d6.} c3 {only critical move.}
10. bxc3 Nxc3 11. Qc2 Nd5 {Some years ago this position was considered unclear,
but now everybody has an engine, and it's clear that White is better:} 12. Rd1
{[%csl Rd8][%cal Ge2e4] our idea is e4, and Black's queen doesn't have a good
square.} (12. Rb1 $5 {deserves attention.}) 12... Bd7 {only move} (12... Qc7 $2
13. Nb5 $18) 13. Bxd5 {The most simple continuation.} (13. Nc4 $5 {also
possible}) 13... exd5 14. Rxd5 Qc7 (14... Be7 $2 {White is winning after many
moves, for example} 15. Bh6 $5 gxh6 16. Rad1 $18) 15. Nc4 {Our idea is Nd6+,
Black has only one move not to lose immediately:} Qc6 {but we can play many
moves like Nd6+, Rd2, or just} 16. e4 Be7 17. Nd6+ Bxd6 18. Rxd6 Qa4 19. Qxc5
Rc8 20. Qd4 $16) 9. Rxd1 Nd5 {Better than Nd7, but not enough for equality:} (
9... Nd7 $2 {300 games, but Nd7 is even worse than Nd5:} 10. Na3 Be7 (10...
Nxe5 11. Bf4 {[%cal Ga3b5]} f6 12. Bxe5 fxe5 13. Nxc4 $18) 11. Nxc4 Rb8 (11...
O-O 12. Bxb7 $18) 12. Be3 O-O 13. b3 $18 {Absolutely winning position. Why?
Because look at Black's development.}) 10. Nc3 {my recommendation because it
looks the most simple direction:} (10. Na3 $5 {also possible.}) (10. a4 $5 {
also possible.}) 10... Nxc3 11. bxc3 Be7 12. a4 $5 $146 {Nobody has tried it,
but it looks to me like a very natural positional move.} (12. Rb1 $14 {also
good.}) 12... Rb8 {better than 00, but still bad position for Black:} (12...
O-O $2 13. a5 {[%csl Ra8,Rc8] we stop Black's development.} Rb8 14. Be3 b5 15.
axb6 axb6 16. Ra7 Rd8 {only move} 17. Rxd8+ Bxd8 18. Kf1 Kf8 19. h4 {Black is
paralyzed, for example:} Be7 20. Bc6 b5 21. Ke1 b4 22. Kd1 b3 23. Kc1 $18 {
Game over. One day, we will take the c4 and c5 pawns.}) 13. a5 Bd7 14. Rb1 b5
15. axb6 Rxb6 (15... axb6 16. Ra1 $16 {[%csl Ra7][%cal Ga1a7] Ra7 next, and
White is winning.}) 16. Be3 $16 {Looks like a very bad endgame for Black. What
can I say... 7...Nxe5 is for sure not a good move. Maybe Black's position is
objectively not lost if he plays engine's moves, but I am confident that we
are better.} *

