1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 c5 6. O-O Nc6 7. Ne5 Bd7 8. Nxc4
cxd4 9. Bf4 Be7 {Black allows Nd6+, but this is also an important line.} 10.
Nd6+ Kf8 {Of course, Kf8 doesn't look great, but the position is concrete.} (
10... Bxd6 $6 {is bad, because after} 11. Bxd6 {[%csl Re8] It is very
difficult for Black to castle, for example:} e5 {[%csl Rd6][%cal Yd7g4]
Black's idea is to move the bishop and attack our Bd6.} 12. Qa4 $1 {[%csl Yc6]
[%cal Ya4c6] Important move. We don't allow Black's bishop to leave the d7
square.} Rc8 {Logical move: Black protects his Nc6.} (12... Ne7 13. Qa3 $14 {
[%csl Re7] Black still cannot castle.}) 13. Nd2 Be6 14. Ba3 $14 {[%csl Re8]
New position and it's not clear how to continue for Black.}) 11. Nxb7 {We must
take the pawn.} Qb6 12. Nd6 {[%csl Rf8] For what do we play? We hope that it's
difficult to play for Black with the king on f8.} Qc5 $1 {Only serious move
for Black. Maybe 12...Rd8 is also possible, but worse for sure.} (12... Nh5 $2
13. Nc4 Qc5 14. Ne5 $1 $18 {Theodorou-Moroni, 2020.}) (12... Qa6 $2 13. b4 $1
Rb8 14. b5 Rxb5 15. Nxb5 Qxb5 16. Nd2 $18 {Anurag-Blohberger, 2017.}) (12...
Nd5 $6 13. Nc4 Qa6 14. Ne5 Be8 15. Bxd5 exd5 16. Nxc6 Bxc6 17. Qxd4 $16 {
Rogers-Toth, 1984.}) (12... Rd8 {Maybe this move is possible, but for sure is
worse than 12...Qc5.} 13. Nd2 e5 $1 $146 (13... Nd5 14. N2c4 $1 $146 Qa6 15.
Bd2 $16 {[%cal Ga2a4,Gd6b5] We can play a4-Nb5 next.}) 14. N6c4 {[%csl Rf8]
Don't forget that Black's king on f8 will need a lot of time to be improved.}
Qc7 15. Bg5 $14 {[%csl Rf8] Looks like a normal position, only that Black's
king is on f8.}) 13. Ne4 {I prefer this move.} (13. b4 {Mainline. b4 looks for
sure interesting, but it was more interesting when it was a novelty; now for
sure everybody has analyzed it deeply.} Qxb4 14. a3 Qc5 15. Qb3 $13 {Theory
continues much further, and Black has more than one good continuation.}) 13...
Nxe4 14. Bxe4 {Now, Black has three logical continuations: e5, f5 or g5.} g5 (
14... e5 15. Bd2 {only good move is} f5 {and we will analyze it in the 14...f5
move order.}) (14... f5 15. Bg2 e5 16. Bd2 {Not easy to play for Black, for
example:} e4 {Looks logical: it closes our bishop, and it prevents our e2-e4.}
(16... Rb8 17. e4 $14 {This is our typical idea.}) (16... Rd8 17. e4 $1 $14) (
16... g5 $2 {Human move, with the idea Kg7, but it's bad:} 17. Na3 (17. e4 $2 {
not good now beause of} f4 $1 $17 {[%csl Rf4]}) 17... Kg7 18. Rc1 Qd6 19. Nc4
Qe6 20. e3 $16 {[%csl Rg7][%cal Ge3d4,Gf1e1] exd4 or Re1 next.}) (16... Kf7 {
Another human move, but bad:} 17. e4 $1 $14) 17. Na3 {[%cal Gf2f3] At some
point, we might consider f3.} Qb6 {best move, but I am not sure everybody will
play it:} 18. f3 (18. Nc4 $5 Qa6 19. b3 $36 {[%cal Yg3g4] Maybe g4 somewhere})
18... Qxb2 {looks very risky for Black} (18... e3 $2 19. Bxe3 $16 {[%csl Rd7]
[%cal Gd1d7]}) 19. Nc4 Qb5 20. Rc1 e3 21. Bxe3 {For the engine this is
possible because of} Be6 $1 {But ok, I hope that we don't play against the
engine!} 22. f4 $5 dxe3 23. Na3 Bxa3 24. Bxc6 Qb8 25. Rb1 Qc8 26. Qa4 Be7 27.
Bb7 Qe8 28. Bc6 $11) 15. Bd2 {[%cal Yb1a3,Ya1c1] What is our idea? Depends on
Black's next move, but most likely Na3-Rc1.} Rb8 $1 {Best move for the engine.}
(15... f5 $2 {Human move, but bad:} 16. Bg2 Kf7 17. Na3 $18 {[%cal Ga1c1]}) (
15... Kg7 $6 {Another human move, but also bad:} 16. Na3 $14 {[%csl Rc5][%cal
Ga1c1]}) 16. Qc1 $5 (16. Na3 Rxb2 17. Rc1 Qxa3 18. Bxc6 Qxa2 19. Bxg5 Bxg5 20.
Qxd4 $11 {must be equal}) 16... Qxc1 17. Rxc1 {We can try to play this endgame}
Rc8 18. Na3 Kg7 19. Nc4 $14 {/= Looks playable. 9...Be7 is objectively a sound
variation, but not too many games have been played here, and practically, it
will be difficult for your opponent to play with the king on f8.} *

