{[%evp 0,33,25,20,27,6,6,6,6,-16,-9,-5,26,0,-1,-4,-6,-14,-2,-16,-3,-15,6,40,37,
39,33,42,54,33,55,19,50,19,43,40]} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 dxc4 5.
Bg2 c6 6. O-O b5 7. Ne5 Bb7 8. b3 cxb3 9. axb3 Be7 10. Nc3 {[%cal Gc3b5] Black
has different moves here.} Qb6 {Second most played option.} (10... O-O {
was played by Tomashevsky against Eljanov, but after} 11. Nxb5 Nd5 12. Na3 {
It is clear that White is better.} c5 {The game continued with 13.Bb2, but I
think that} 13. dxc5 {is even stronger.} Bxc5 14. Bb2 Nd7 15. Nd3 Be7 16. Nc4 {
[%csl Gb2,Gg2] Our pieces are much better, especially the bishops.} Bf6 17. Qd2
Bxb2 18. Qxb2 {You need to get used to these positions, it looks like equal
