1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 a6 6. Ne5 Bb4+ 7. Nc3 Nd5 8. Bd2
b5 {This is Black's second most common continuation. I believe that the
arizing positions are very playable for us.} 9. O-O Bxc3 {necessary move.} (
9... O-O $4 {is impossible because of} 10. Nxd5 $1 Bxd2 11. Nxc7 $18) (9... Be7
$2 {also not good because of} 10. Nxd5 exd5 11. e4 $1 Bb7 12. exd5 Bxd5 13.
Nxf7 $1 {key move.} Kxf7 (13... Bxf7 14. Bxa8 $18) 14. Qh5+ $18) (9... Bb7 $6
10. Nxd5 Bxd2 11. Nf6+ gxf6 12. Bxb7 fxe5 (12... Ra7 13. Nc6 $18) 13. Bxa8 Qxd4
14. Qc2 $16) 10. bxc3 O-O (10... Bb7 $6 {inaccurate move order} 11. e4 Nf6 12.
Bg5 h6 13. Bxf6 gxf6 (13... Qxf6 14. Nxc4 $1 $16 bxc4 $2 15. e5 $18) 14. Ng4
Nd7 15. Ne3 $14 {[%cal Yd4d5,Re8g8,Yd1h5] It will be difficult for Black to
castle because of Qh5, and we might consider the move d4-d5 very soon.}) (10...
f6 $2 {f6 is usually strategically dubious, but here it's just a losing move:}
11. e4 $1 Ne7 12. Qh5+ g6 13. Nxg6 $1 Nxg6 14. f4 $18) 11. a4 {my
recommendation.} ({some players have tried} 11. e4 {which is a natural move,
but not White's best option because of} Nb6 $132 {[%cal Gc8b7] Bb7 next, and
Black is immediately more than fine.}) 11... f6 {This is one of the very few
moments in our database where the move f7-f6 is necessary.} (11... c6 12. e4
Nb6 13. a5 N6d7 14. f4 Bb7 15. Be3 $14) (11... Bb7 12. Qb1 f6 (12... c6 $2 13.
Nxc4 $16) 13. Nf3 {trans in 11...f6.}) 12. Nf3 (12. Ng4 {[%csl Yg4] Has also
been tried, but I am not sure if the knight is well placed on g4.}) 12... Bb7 (
12... c6 $6 13. e4 Nb6 14. a5 N6d7 15. e5 $16) 13. Qb1 $5 {We want to provoke
c7-c6.} c6 (13... Qd7 {What is Black's next move? c6 is necessary in my
opinion.} 14. h4 $5 $14 {[%csl Rb8] It's impossible for Black to develop the
Knight on b8, so c6 will be anyway necessary.}) 14. h4 Nd7 15. h5 {[%cal Gh5h6]
Very interesting new position, which is not easy to play for Black. Our idea
is h5-h6, and it seems that Black's best continuation is to stop it by playing}
h6 {After which we can play} 16. Nh4 $36 {Our compensation is out of question,
but objectively, we don't have an advantage. Still, it's a new position, and
over the board it's not so easy to play for Black. We can consider many ideas
like e4 and then f4-g4-g5, or Bc1-Ba3.} *

