14. Qxc4 {Black can play Qd6 or Rxb2, and very big theory. I don't like to
play it because it's too forced. I prefer more flexible lines for play.}) 9...
Bd7 $1 (9... O-O $2 {normal move, but serious mistake} 10. a3 Nd5 11. Qxc4 {
Advantage}) (9... a6 10. Ne5 Bd7 $1 {also important position, but we will see
it in another move order} (10... O-O $2 {Dubov-Bluebaum} 11. a3 Nxe5 12. dxe5
Nd5 13. Qxc4 $16 {Seriously better for White.})) (9... Rb8 $2 {Just bad because
} 10. a3 {[%cal Rb7b5] And Black doesn't have b5.}) 10. O-O {Now, Black has
two serious lines} a5 {The most popular move.} (10... a6 {also serious line}
11. Ne5 b5 12. Qa3 Rb8 $1 {We'll analyze it in "Position 5" of this Unit.}) 11.
