Qc3 $5 {My recommendation. Why? Because Qd3 was played 200 times, Qc3 only 15,
and these two moves have the same strength.} (8. Qd3 {We can check the
mainline.} c5 9. O-O (9. dxc5 {was played by Vidit, but it's not interesting,
in my opinion:} Bxc5 10. Ne5 {We want to play for two bishops.} Qb6 $1 11. Nxd7
(11. O-O Bb5 $13) 11... Bxf2+ 12. Kf1 Nxd7 13. e3 Ne5 14. Qe4 Qb5+ 15. Kxf2
Nd3+ 16. Kf3 Ne5+ 17. Kf2 Nd3+ $11 {draw by repetition.}) 9... Bc6 {Most
common continuation. Now I can recommend} (9... Rc8 10. Nc3 cxd4 11. Nxd4 ({
also possible is} 11. Qxd4 Bc5 12. Qh4 O-O (12... Be7 13. Ne5 $1 $16) 13. Rd1
Nc6 14. Bg5 Be7 15. Qf4 $14 {Looks slightly better.}) 11... Bc5 {most logical
move} 12. Ne4 Nxe4 13. Bxe4 Bc6 $1 14. Nxc6 Qxd3 15. Bxd3 Nxc6 16. Bd2 $14 {
[%csl Gd2,Gd3] We can play a long game with two bishops.}) 10. Bd2 $5 {Which
is very rare, but strong.} cxd4 {and now, important move} 11. Rc1 $1 {We wait
for the right moment to play Qxd4.} Qb6 $1 {best for Black.} 12. Qxd4 Bxf3 13.
Qa4+ (13. Qxb6 $5 axb6 14. Bxf3 Nb3 $1 15. Bxb7 Ra7 16. Bc6+ Kd8 17. Nc3 Nxa1
18. Rxa1 {Compensation, but not advantage for the engine. But maybe it could
be a try for a real game.} Rc7 19. Bf3 Rd7 $1 {Black's idea is Be3-Bc5,
Bf4-Bd6.} 20. Be1 $5 $13 {Playable.} (20. Be3 Bc5 21. Bf4 Bd6 $11)) 13... Bc6
14. Qxa5 Rc8 15. Qxb6 axb6 16. a4 $14 {[%csl Rb6,Rb7][%cal Gb1a3,Ga3c4] Of
course, it's not a huge advantage, but we can definitely play a long game
against Black's doubled 'b' pawns. Na3-Nc4 could be our plan.}) 8... Nd5 (8...
c5 $2 {not good now because of} 9. Bd2 {[%csl Ra5]} b6 10. dxc5 Rc8 11. b4 $16)
9. Qd3 {[%csl Rd5] We have included Black's move Nd5, but knight on d5 not
always stays better than on f6.} c5 10. O-O {[%cal Gf3e5] Some questions for
Black.} (10. Nc3 $5 {deserves attention} Nxc3 11. bxc3 cxd4 12. cxd4 Bb4+ 13.
Bd2 Bxd2+ 14. Nxd2 $132 {Playable, a bit more pleasant, but objectively fine
for Black.}) 10... Nb4 {Probably Black's best option.} (10... cxd4 11. Nxd4 $14
{looks better for us.}) (10... Be7 $2 11. dxc5 Bxc5 12. Nc3 {[%csl Rd5] Nd5 is
tempo for us, not for him.} Nb4 13. Qb1 $18 {[%cal Ga2a3] a3 is our next move.}
) (10... Bc6 11. dxc5 Bxc5 12. a3 $14) 11. Qd1 cxd4 12. a3 Nd5 {only move.} (
12... Nbc6 $2 13. Nbd2 {[%csl Ra5][%cal Gb2b4] b4 is coming.} b6 14. b4 Nb7 15.
Bb2 $18 {[%csl Rb7]}) 13. b4 $5 $146 (13. Nxd4 Be7 14. Bxd5 exd5 15. Nc3 {
Black cannot save the pawn.} O-O 16. Nxd5 Bc5 {Black plays for compensation,
