19. Rfb1 $14 {Our pieces are more active.}) 15. Rfb1 $5 $146 {My novelty. We
wait for his reaction, and it's useful move against Nxc3. Also we can consider
Nxc4 or Nxd5. But the most important thing is that we have a new position. In
my opinion, Black has only two good moves: Qe8 or Nb6, but we will check also
a lot of other moves that your opponent could play.} (15. Nxd5 {White's
automatic continuation, but Black is fine after} exd5 16. Bxd5 Bh3 $1 {Maybe
it was interesting when it was a new position, but now there are already 30
games of strong players, and this continuation is well-known.}) (15. Nxc4 $2 {
huge blunder because of} Nxc3 16. bxc3 Bb5 $19) 15... Nb6 {In the worst case,
you will face this move, because nobody will even consider 15...Qe8, trust me.}
(15... b5 16. Nxd5 exd5 17. Bxd5 c6 18. Nxd7 Qxd7 19. Bg2 $14 {Looks very
interesting for White.}) (15... a3 {Human move.} 16. Nxd5 exd5 17. Bxd5 Bf5 18.
e4 $14) (15... Qe7 {also human move, but after} 16. Nxc4 Nxc4 17. Qxc4 c6 18.
a3 $14 {We have a small but long-term advantage.}) (15... Be8 16. Nxc4 Nxc4 17.
Qxc4 $14) (15... Nxc3 16. bxc3 $14) (15... Ra6 16. Nxc4 $14) (15... Qe8 {
One of the two best moves, but it's very difficult to believe that somebody
will play Qe8.} 16. Qc2 (16. Nxd5 exd5 17. Bxd5 Be6 $1 18. Bg2 f6 19. Nf3 Bd5
20. Nd2 $11) 16... Nb6 17. Rd1 $44 {Compensation and playable, but no
