cxd4 6. O-O Be7 {The bishop on e7 is worse than on c5.} 7. cxd5 Nxd5 (7... exd5
{is not great.} 8. Nxd4 $14 {Another improved Tarrasch.}) 8. Nxd4 O-O {[%csl
Gd4,Re7] And it is clear the difference: our knight on d4 is not under attack,
as it will be in the 6...Bc5 variation, for this reason, we can now play} 9.
Qb3 $1 {[%csl Yc5] A move which will not be possible in the 6...Bc5 variation.}
