{[%evp 0,31,20,20,20,18,18,18,18,-2,19,-6,18,13,30,30,25,29,29,34,27,30,28,39,
25,25,62,23,32,22,2,25,42,41]} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 c5 5. Bg2
cxd4 6. O-O Bc5 $1 {[%csl Yd4][%cal Yc5d4] The best option.} 7. Nxd4 (7. cxd5
Nxd5 8. Nxd4 O-O {[%csl Gd4][%cal Yc5d4,Yd1b3] We cannot play Qb3 here.}) 7...
O-O (7... dxc4 {was tried in Gelfand-Aronian, but it is not inspiring.} 8. Qa4+
Qd7 9. Nb5 O-O (9... a6 $4 10. Nc7+ $18) 10. Qxc4 Qe7 11. b4 $1 {Very
important move, the only that gives an advantage.} Bb6 (11... Bxb4 $2 12. Nc7
$18 {[%csl Yc7][%cal Gc4c7]}) 12. N5c3 $1 $146 {[%csl Yc3,Re7][%cal Gc1a3,
Gb4b5] is strong, White's knight was not good on b5 anymore.} (12. a4 {was
played in all 4 games, but we have a stronger option.}) 12... a5 (12... Nc6 $2
13. Ba3 $18 {[%cal Gb4b5]}) (12... e5 13. Bg5 {The position is very unpleasant.
} Be6 14. Nd5 Bxd5 15. Bxf6 Qxf6 16. Bxd5 {The bishop is very strong on d5.}
Nc6 17. e3 Rac8 18. Qb3 $16 {[%csl Yb6,Gd5][%cal Gb1c3]}) 13. Na4 $16 {[%csl
Gb1][%cal Gb4b5,Gc1a3]}) 8. Nb3 {[%csl Yc5] First we clarify where Black will
retreat the bishop.} (8. cxd5 {We transpose to something we don't like.} Nxd5)
8... Be7 {played only in 4 games, but more precise, in my opinion.} (8... Bb6 {
is more played, but less precise.} 9. Nc3 Nc6 (9... dxc4 10. Qxd8 Rxd8 11. Nd2
$14 {[%csl Rc4,Gg2][%cal Gd2c4,Gg2a8] We will retake the pawn and be slightly
better. You can check Deac-Dragnev, 2023, it was a rapid game, but it
highlights the ideas.}) 10. Bg5 {is easier.} (10. cxd5 {Maybe Black has some
compensation, even if it is not easy.} Nxd5 11. Nxd5 exd5 12. Qxd5 Qxd5 13.
Bxd5 $14) 10... dxc4 11. Nd2 h6 12. Bxf6 Qxf6 13. Nxc4 {The position is very
pleasant.} Bc7 14. Nb5 Be5 {Engine move, but quite strange.} (14... Bb8 15. Qa4
$14) 15. Qb3 a6 16. Nc3 Bxc3 17. bxc3 $14 {[%csl Rc8,Gg2] Engine thinks it is
not over, but +0.50 is enough advantage, typical Catalan position.}) 9. cxd5 {
Now we can take on d5.} Nxd5 (9... exd5 $2 {is very bad.} 10. Nc3 $16 {[%csl
Rd5]}) 10. Bd2 $5 {An improvement over the Gukesh game.} (10. e4 {was played
in both high level games, Gukesh-Nepo, Candidates 2024 and Mendonca-Yakkuboev,
Abu Dhabi 2024.} Nb4 11. Nc3 {Both games continued with N8c6, but} Qxd1 $1 $146
{is completely equal, I cannot find anything for White.} 12. Rxd1 N8c6 13. a3 {
Probably they were scared of this move, but here} Nc2 $1 {The knight gets back
into the game.} 14. Rb1 e5 $1 $11 {No chance at all.}) 10... Nc6 11. Nc3 {
[%csl Gc3][%cal Yd5c3,Yd2c3] We prepared Nc3, I still think that taking is the
best.} Nxc3 $1 (11... Nf6 {Black simply has worse pieces.} 12. Rc1 e5 13. Be3 {
[%csl Yd5][%cal Gg2a8] Now the d5 square is also a problem.} Be6 14. Nc5 $16) (
11... Bf6 12. Rc1 $14 {It doesn't look well for Black.}) 12. Bxc3 Qb6 $1 (12...
Bf6 $2 {is a big mistake.} 13. Qxd8 Rxd8 14. Bxf6 gxf6 15. Rfd1 {The endgame
is simply over.} Bd7 16. Nc5 $18) 13. Nd4 {Only 2 games, but it is the best
Black can achieve in my opinion.} Nb4 $1 {is the strongest, played in one
email game.} (13... Rd8 {is critical, but not good.} 14. Nxc6 $1 Rxd1 15. Nxe7+
Kf8 16. Rfxd1 Kxe7 17. Bd4 $1 {[%csl Re7] Only rook and bishop for king, but
the king is very unsafe.} (17. Bxg7 {is not good.} Bd7 $1 $11) 17... Qa5 (17...
Qa6 18. Rac1 $18 {[%csl Rc7][%cal Gc1c7]}) 18. Bxg7 {Now, b7 is hanging.} Bd7
19. Bxb7 {[%csl Gb2][%cal Gg7b2] Now we have 2 pawns to go with our pieces, so
it for sure cannot be equal ever for Black.} Rd8 20. Bf3 f6 21. Bh6 $16 {
[%csl Gh6][%cal Gh6e3] The bishop gets back into the game.}) (13... Bd7 {
is met with} 14. Nf5 $1 {We win the dark squares bishop.} Rfd8 15. Nxe7+ Nxe7
16. Qd2 {The c3 bishop is very strong.} Bc6 17. Qg5 $1 {Nice tempo.} Nf5 18.
Bxc6 Qxc6 {[%csl Gc3,Rf5]} 19. Qg4 $14 {[%cal Ge2e4] Not so easy to coordinate
with Black.}) 14. e3 $5 {is my recommendation, with the idea to improve the
queen.} Rd8 15. Qg4 Bf8 16. Nb3 $14 {Engine shows +0.20, it is playable for
Black of course, but we are in a new terittory for many moves, and it is not
easy to play like a computer to keep this evaluation. Maybe if more games will
start being played in this position, you will need to check deeper, but for
today's current state of theory, this is more than enough.} *

